.name
WhereK
.author
Kenneth J McCormick 
.version
3.0
.distribution
Freeware
.description
A highly configurable hard drive utility.  Features an automatic disk
cataloger with 3 modes, turns directories into ascii files that can be
saved and searched, allows other programs to run while continuing in the
background, creates lists with versions of the libraries on your hard drive
and disks.  All files created can be saved.  Features 2 help modes,
individual help for keys and a comprehensive help mode, both accessible
from the program.  Runs on WB2.0+ except for the Library Versions Bulk
Lister which requires WB3.0 and above.  
